      "content": "A thread count of 800 is certainly high, but a loose weave in certain sections of Egyptian cotton could be a sign of a few things. It's not always normal, even for super-fine specifications, and you should definitely check your loom settings to see if there's a tension issue. Sometimes, the warp or weft tension can fluctuate, causing those areas to relax more than others. Adjusting the tension settings might bring that weave back to the tight, consistent feel you expect.",
