    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The density of the weave absolutely impacts more than just the hand-feel; it's a key factor in durability too. A consistent, tight weave creates a denser fabric, which generally translates to better resistance against wear and tear. If the density is inconsistent, you risk areas that are more porous, which could lead to faster wear, absorb more moisture, or even weaken under stress. It's a critical structural element, not just a surface characteristic.",
      "source": "target",
